{"id":14881372,"mediaExerciseId":"3ca9d2f0-c0ab-40d5-ac87-67067f81a355","exerciseName":"1","chapterName":"12","chapterTitle":"Some Lessons From Capital Market History","groupId":612365,"groupTitle":"Minicase Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":419,"solutions":[{"id":6249757,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will define and compare the differences between a mutual fund and a company stock.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A mutual fund is a type of investment where the investors pool their money and allow the manager of the fund to invest the collected money into different assets.\n\nOn the other hand, a company stock refers to ownership of a part of a company. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"Mutual funds have an advantage over company stocks since it can be diversified. This means that your money can be invested in multiple different fields.\n\nFor the same amount of money, you can gain more diverse holdings compared to buying a stock of a single company. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"Aside from that, mutual funds already have managers so you will not need to invest much time into analyzing the market movement since the manager already does that for you. \n\nThe downside however is that you cannot handpick the type of stock and each transaction, you pay a percentage to the manager as their fee for managing the funds. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"48cd02f9-7397-4033-b82f-7ff588734267","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881373,"exerciseName":"2","page":419,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"2da93770-5943-490f-8bcc-7a7ef3f229bb","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-minicase-questions-2-2da93770-5943-490f-8bcc-7a7ef3f229bb"},{"id":14881374,"exerciseName":"3","page":419,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"86c2cfbc-6caa-4bcb-a313-c419295f1555","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-minicase-questions-3-86c2cfbc-6caa-4bcb-a313-c419295f1555"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881370,"exerciseName":"24","page":418,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"eb97fb84-235c-44b7-886a-3ca90eba5ed4","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-minicase-questions-24-eb97fb84-235c-44b7-886a-3ca90eba5ed4"},{"id":14881369,"exerciseName":"23","page":418,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"aa490f47-7d02-4d20-aaa3-d097816c5522","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-12-minicase-questions-23-aa490f47-7d02-4d20-aaa3-d097816c5522"}],"_w